header.gameNote: O'REILLY AUTO PARTS CBE CLASSIC AT HARRISONBURG VA

article.headline: Presbyterian 69, Princeton 67
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Al'Lonzo Coleman scored 17 points, including the go-ahead basket with 16 seconds left, to lead Presbyterian to a 69-67 victory over Princeton on Wednesday. Josh Johnson's free throw with 2 seconds to go sealed the win for the Blue Hose (2-4) in the O'Reilly Auto Parts CBE Classic. Khalid Mutakabbir added 16 points for Presbyterian, which led 64-57 with 3:59 remaining. The Tigers (2-3) then used a 7-0 run, including six points by Ian Hummer, to tie the game with 1:30 left. After Pierre Miller made two free throws for the Blue Hose, Princeton took the lead on a Douglas Davis 3-pointer with 28 seconds to go. Coleman then hit his game-winner. Presbyterian held Princeton's leading scorer, Dan Mavraides, who was averaging 15.8 points per game, to five points on 2-for-11 shooting. Hummer had 24 points on 10-for-13 shooting, plus 14 rebounds, and Davis had 23 points.
